ref: Conf: 2.Conf.on Neutron Physics, Kiev 1973, Vol.4, p.57 (1973)
title: Energy spectra and average prompt neutron number for fission of curium isotopes

x4codes.shortRef: Conf: 2.Conf.on Neutron Physics, Kiev 1973, Vol.4, p.57 (1973)

x4freetext: No INDC(CCP) rep. for this conf.proc. at NDS web-site.
Energy spectra and average prompt neutron number
Time-of-flight method.Flight base is equal 50 cm.
of fission fragments and plastic scintillation detector
of 100 mm diameter, 30 mm length for prompt neutrons
Spectrum of fission neutrons was approximated
here E - energy of fission neutrons,
N(E) - a number of fission neutrons with
For U-235 value of T is equal 1.29 MeV.
For definition of average number of prompt fission
neutrons spectrum of fission neutrons was been
integrated and this result was regarded to number
of fissions registered at the time of measurements.
